 **************************************************************/


 ****************************************************************
 *			FUNCTIONS				*
 ****************************************************************

find_u(t)		returns t, after scanning over chains of bound
			variables.

clear_bindings_u()	Clear out the binding list.  This should be used
			before unifications, if the binding list might not
			be clear.

undo_bindings_u(m)	Undo all bindings in the binding list from m to the
			top.

basic_unify_u(a,b,r)	unifies types *a and *b, treating null values as
			unbound variables.  No occur check is done.
			If r is true, all bindings are placed in the 
			binding list for possible undoing later.
			If in_overlap is true, variables 
			left_nontriv_bound and right_nontriv_bound 
			are set if there is a restrictive 
			binding on the left and/or right, respectively.

unify_u(a,b,r)		unifies *a with *b.  Null values of a and b are
			treated like unbound type variables.
			Sets variables left_bound and right_bound as 
			basic_unify.  If in_overlap is true, also undoes
			the bindings that were done.
			If r = TRUE, then bindings are recorded for possible
			undoing later.

overlap_u(a,b)		Returns an indication of how varieties a and b
			overlap.  
			  DISJOINT_OV	  - a and b are disjoint
			  EQUAL_OV	  - a = b
			  CONTAINS_OV	  - b is a proper subset of a
			  CONTAINED_IN_OV - a is a proper subset of b
			  BAD_OV	  - none of the above.

Remark: See the remark in infer.c concerning special behavior of 
basic_unify_u.


